						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the wall of the Vīrabhadra temple.</p>						

						<p>Sōmēśvara IV, 1184-85 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is engraved below No. 135 below and it is treated here as a separate record. It is dated Śaka 1106, Krōdhi, other details being lost. This date corresponds to 1184-85 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records gifts including one of money to the god Prasanna-Kēśava. The inscription is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
